[I can. It was an error on my part in not editing out that silly term in
the first place. Paraguay is land-locked and therefore might have weeds
around bodies of water but not around sea water. Subscriber Mike O'Dell
also pointed out that Paraguay is land-locked. The other country in South
America that has no ocean front properties is Bolivia. I agree with Bill
Messer on the other points he makes as well. The posting was taken from a
newspaper report and is not up to scientific standards, which may also be
the case for the Minister's comments. I could not find recent mention of
dengue in Paraguay and have no idea whether a prior epidemic of one or
another of the four dengue viruses might have primed the immunologic pump
there. Anyone know? - Mod. CHC
